are such that there is maximal screening with a vanishing
interaction potential. As  increases, the potential
decreases and the interaction force between two twisted sectors 
decreases.
Finally the potential is proportional to the radius of the
compactified fifth dimensional gauge theory  which sets its 
dynamical scale. 



The rectangular Wilson Loop at Strong Coupling 

Dual  metric deconstruction 
We have seen that in the large  limit, deconstructed 
quiver theories become similar to a fifth dimensional gauge theories.
We will now analyse the models in the large gauge coupling limit
using the AdS/CFT correspondence.
To simplify the analytic treatment we shall concentrate on the case where 
the
orbifold group acts on a single complex plane. 
The metric due to the presence of the displaced branes is given by
 
where
 
and   is the location of the i-th image 
of the 
displaced brane. 
The complement metric  is defined up to the orbifold 
identifications.
In the case where the orbifold acts on a single plane we denote by 
 the
polar angle in that plane. 
We are interested in computing the Wilson line between quarks 
belonging to different sectors. In the orbifold cover this amounts
to putting quarks in sectors separated by an angle which is a multiple of
