At strong coupling the relevant regime is the blown-up vicinity of the 
displaced 
brane where 
 
while the quarks lie at infinity. 

There are various 
relevant regions. Far away from the branes, space-time becomes
isometric to . The quarks are on the
boundary of . In the interior of the six extra dimensions,
the geometry departs from the  behaviour. In particular
there is a ring around the stacks of branes where the harmonic
function signals the presence of a fifth dimension. The geometrical 
setting in 
the orbifold plane has 
been
sketched in Fig.3.


